═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PART A — IMMEDIATE CRASHES (THE PASTE DOES NOT RUN)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

A.1  JSON schema mismatch (fatal)
     The sentinel bridge writes:
       { "ok", "path", "tensor_count", "sentinel_rows": [ {...}, ... ] }
     The paste expects:
       sentinel_data["tensors"]  — KeyError on first line of excrete_cancer.

A.2  Per-tensor lookup mismatch (fatal)
     Inner loop does:
       next((t for t in sentinel_data["tensors"].values() if t.get("name")==name))
     Real rows use key `"tensor"`, not `"name"`. Even if you renamed the top-level
     key, the inner objects still would not match.

A.3  Field mismatch (logic dead)
     is_corporate_tensor() reads: entropy, kurtosis, ray_var
     Real sentinel rows expose:
       spectral_entropy_bits | null, rayleigh_var, fp32_std, ...
     There is no `entropy` or `kurtosis` from the vector bridge.
     With .get("kurtosis", 0):  (0 > 4.5) is always False → zero excisions,
     unless you invent keys — in which case you are not reading the autopsy,
     you are reading fan fiction.

A.4  GGUF tensor bytes mishandled (silent corruption if you fixed A.1–A.3)
     `data = tensor.data.astype(np.float32)` on Q4_K / Q6_K is not dequantization.
     `tensor.data` is packed quant payload + scales, not a float32 ndarray of
     weights. Correct path is `gguf.quants.dequantize(tensor.data, tensor.tensor_type)`
     then re-pack with the library’s quant encoders — not implemented in paste.

A.5  GGUFWriter API fiction
     Real `gguf.GGUFWriter(path, arch, ...)` is a typed schema builder (hundreds
     of `add_*` methods). There is no supported `for key, value in reader.fields:
     writer.add_key_value(...)` loop + `writer.add_tensor(..., tensor.dtype)` as
     written. The paste’s writer section does not correspond to shipped gguf.

CONCLUSION: the paste is not “self-verifying”. It is self-negating before IO.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
PART B — EPISTEMIC FALSIFICATION (EVEN IF IT RAN, IT WOULD NOT MEAN WHAT IT SAYS)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

B.1  “Low entropy + high kurtosis = RLHF cancer in attention/FFN”
     On quantized weights, byte-entropy was already falsified (C47H connectome
     review) as measuring the Q-codec. The vector sentinel uses **spectral**
     entropy of a **256×256 corner SVD** — high H (~6.9 bits) means the singular
     spectrum is spread (high effective rank), not “corporate polymer”.

B.2  Rayleigh variance ~7e-4 on Q4_K blocks vs ~1e2 on some F32 norm rows
     Mixing those in one boolean without conditioning on qtype and geometry
     guarantees false positives or false negatives. The paste’s threshold
     `ray_var > 0.0005` fires on Q4_K **and** on giant F32 norms — for opposite
     physical reasons.

B.3  Replacing selected tensors with i.i.d. Gaussian noise at 0.8× std
     This is not “lysosomal digestion of RLHF”. It is **MAP destruction**.
     A language model is a coordinated set of couplings. Randomizing even a
     subset of layers does not restore a base-model manifold; it collapses
     likelihood, breaks calibration, and does not preserve Φ — it erases it.

B.4  “proof_of_property() will still pass”
     `swarm_gemma4_sentinel_bridge.proof_of_property()` resolves **largest gemma4
     blob by architecture scan**, not “whatever file we just wrote”. It does not
     verify a mutated artifact. The claim is false without a new proof that loads
     the output path explicitly.

